# `CythonPP`, a C++ interface for python library

`CythonPP` is a library for mapping C++ class/function for python.

## Requirements

`CythonPP` header is written in C++11 so you need a C++11 compiler like [Clang](http://clang.llvm.org/) or [GCC](http://gcc.gnu.org/).
`CythonPP` interface code is written in cython and require cython and numpy 

## Install

You can download the sources directly from github:

    git clone https://github.com/raplonu/CythonPP.git


